  "id": "019cf625-7dd3-7a72-90bd-3a92265ef18e",
  "content": "o test -p corvia-kernel filter_tests -- --nocapture`\nExpected: PASS\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Wire post-filter into `VectorRetriever` and `GraphExpandRetriever`**\n\nIn each retriever's `retrieve` method, after the visibility/RBAC filtering and before returning, add:\n\n```rust\n// Post-filter by metadata (docs workflow: Option A)\nlet results = post_filter_metadata(\n    results,\n    opts.content_role.as_deref(),\n    opts.source_origin.as_deref(),\n);\n```\n\nFor the over-fetch mitigation (spec says `limit * 3`), adjust the limit passed to the store search:\n\n```rust\nlet search_limit = if opts.content_role.is_some() || opts.source_origin.is_some() {\n    opts.limit * 3  // over-fetch to compensate for post-filter\n} else {\n    opts.limit\n};\n```\n\nThen truncate after filtering: `results.truncate(opts.limit);`\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Run full kernel tests**\n\nRun: `cd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo test -p corvia-kernel`\nExpected: All tests pass\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/retriever.rs crates/corvia-kernel/src/rag_types.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(kernel): add metadata post-filter to retrieval pipeline\"\n```\n\n---\n",
